post_text:
Online Registration for Returning Students

Parents Please Complete

REMINDER:

ALL students' parents (new and returning) MUST complete our new online registration. Parents will find the forms once you login to your Lumen Parent Portal. Once you complete the forms, please don't forget to click "submit". This includes the Parent Permission for Computer/Internet Usage Form. This form must be completed and submitted, before your student will be able to take home a device. If you are unable to access Lumen, have forgotten your login information, or do not have access, please contact the school, so we are able to assist you in this new process. Thank you to everyone who has already completed the online registration for their children and we look forward to getting our Wildcat students back tomorrow. Wildcat Strong! #gemcity

Parent Lumen Login Link: https://diamond-mo.lumentouchhosts.com/light/lumen/signin

post_text:
Parents:
We will be having a ‚ÄúBeep and Greet‚Äù on Thursday, August 20th from 5:30-7 for students pre-k through 5th grade. Although we would prefer to have a traditional Open House, due to recommendations by DESE, the CDC, and Newton County Health Department we are making some modifications.
Parents and students, please enter South Main off of 59 Highway by the High School. You will then drive north in front of the Middle School and Elementary building. There will be a location set up where everyone will be able to meet the classroom teacher. We will also be handing out Parent Pick Up tags and providing other information in regards to Free/Reduced lunch and Transportation.
Students will need to plan on bringing classroom supplies the first day of school as we will not be able to take them that evening. First day supplies should include pencils, crayons, and paper. All other supplies can be brought to school at a later time.
If you have questions, please call the Elementary Office at 325-5189.
Thanks!

Parents/Guardians:
Diamond Elementary will be holding a ‚Äúlimited‚Äù Open House for students attending Pre-K, Kindergarten, and new students to the District from 5:30-7 on August 20th. We will be hosting this by appointment only, so if you would like to attend it is important that you call and make an appointment. We will be limiting 4 families per teacher at a time to reduce trace contact. Plans are also underway to determine the best route for your child to ‚Äúmeet‚Äù his/her new teacher. Those plans will be shared soon.
Moving Mountains will also be available that evening. Please refer to their FB page for details.
New student registration begins online tomorrow, August 10th. Class lists will be shared once new students are enrolled to assure classes are of equal size.
We know this is very different and we appreciate your understanding.

Any student (grades 9-12) who did not have contact with Mrs. Slagle (high school counselor), either via email or Zoom meetings last Spring to select Fall 2020 classes, will need to call Mrs. Slagle at 417-325-5188 (ext. 3005) or make an appointment to meet with her in order to create a schedule. The Home Bleachers will be ticketed. You must present ticket at entrance of bleachers to access them. Today graduates were given an envelope with 5 tickets a piece to distribute to their families.

Graduation is optional students and families.

post_text:
Bright Flight Eligibility for 2020 Seniors - The Bright Flight Scholarship requires students to achieve a qualifying ACT of SAT score by the
June national test date of their senior year in high school. However, in response to the
adjustments made by ACT and the College Board, the Missouri Department of Higher Education
and Workforce Development is extending the date on which 2020 seniors may achieve a
qualifying ACT score for the Bright Flight Scholarship to the July national test date. The 2020
seniors who achieve a qualifying ACT score on the July national test date and who are otherwise
eligible can receive the scholarship. Scores achieved on the July 2020 national test date will also
be considered when determining eligibility for this year‚Äôs sophomores and juniors, as has
always been the case.

As a reminder, the qualifying scores for the 2020 seniors are:

Top 3% of graduating class - 31 ACT Composite Score
Top 4th & 5th Percentiles of graduating class - 30 ACT Composite Score

Davenport Scholarship
This is a one year non-renewable scholarship that will be awarded to a senior of Diamond R-IV School District. To be eligible, the student must have a minimum 2.0 GPA at the end of seven semesters; display qualities of good character; citizenship and involvement in school activities; and must be accepted and enrolled at an approved college or university. The amount of this award may vary. The award will be paid to the student upon proof of college attendance.

Attn All Seniors: Mrs. Slagle shared the google form for this scholarship application to your emails. If you're interested, please complete and submit it by April 17th, 11:59 P.M. If you have any questions, please contact tslagle@diamondwildcats.org.

post_text: Good morning, Wildcats! We wanted to make you aware of a few things going on at school to help students stay in the learning mode while we are all quarantined. Our teachers have been preparing work students can do for enrichment. Teachers are primarily using Google classroom and other online resources, but teachers have also prepared paper copies of activities for those families who may not have access to the internet. For those students who plan to work online but need a Chromebook, Chromebooks will be made available for pick-up at the high school library on Monday, March 23, starting at 10:00am. If you would rather have the paper copies, please contact Central Office at 417-325-5186 and the message will get conveyed to the buildings. Many students have already been accessing the online learning. Feel free to email your teachers with any questions.

George Washington Carver Birthplace Memorial Scholarship 2020/2021 -
Amount: $1,000.00
Due Date: March 31, 2020
This scholarship recognizes outstanding public service in honor of Dr. George Washington Carver.

Requirements:
1. Must be pursuing study in one of the following disciplines: Science, Art, Agriculture, Religion, Music, or Education.
2. Must attend an accredited 2 or 4 year college within 100 miles of George Washington Carver National Monument; or attend Iowa State University or Simpson College in Indianola, Iowa.

See Mrs. Slagle or the scholarship box in Ms. G's room for an application.

post_text:
Missouri Girls State and Missouri Boys State
Each year the American Legion Auxiliary holds a week-long intensive study of government and Americanism at the University of Central Missouri in Warrensburg for junior students. This year the sessions will be held June 13th -20th for boys and June 21st - June 27th for girls. The local American Legion covers all costs associated with the event (excluding transportation to and from the campus.)

Qualifications for consideration include: leadership, character, scholarship, and citizenship. Students who attend the session in its entirety are then eligible to apply for many scholarships offered to them in the Fall.

Students who wish to be considered for the event should contact Mrs. Slagle ASAP for more information. Applications must be received in Jefferson City no later than March 1, 2020.
